{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Bacterial binding protein-dependent transport systems [[cite:PUB00000042], [cite:PUB00002368]] are multicomponent systems typically composed of a periplasmic substrate-binding protein, one or two reciprocally homologous integral inner-membrane proteins and one or two peripheral membrane ATP-binding proteins that couple energy to the active transport system. The integral inner-membrane proteins translocate the substrate across the membrane. It has been shown [[cite:PUB00001137], [cite:PUB00003865]] that most of these proteins contain a conserved region located about 80 to 100 residues from their C-terminal extremity. This region seems to be located in a cytoplasmic loop between two transmembrane domains [[cite:PUB00003831]]. Apart from the conserved region, the sequence of these proteins is quite divergent, and they have a variable number of transmembrane helices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This entry describes a subfamily of both CysT and CysW, paralogous and generally tandemly encoded permease proteins of the sulphate ABC transporter [[cite:PUB00035343], [cite:PUB00035344]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR035906", "name" "MetI-like superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR30406" "SULFATE TRANSPORT SYSTEM PERMEASE PROTEIN"}, "ncbifam" {"TIGR00969" "sulfate ABC transporter permease subunit"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Sulphate ABC transporter permease protein 2", "short" "Sulph_transpt2"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 3153, "taxa" 14514, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 27334, "sets" 0, "proteins" 27325, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 21510}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR005667", :literature {"PUB00000042" {"URL" n